015\"],\n      \"suggestions\": [\"Specify the UV wavelength regime and sulfide photochemistry mechanism more clearly\", \"Consider whether H\u2082S availability at surface is consistent with the setting\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"best_pathway_id\": \"P6\",\n  \"overall_confidence\": 0.86,\n  \"network_feedback\": \"This is an exceptionally well-designed synthesis network that demonstrates comprehensive coverage of the prebiotic alanine literature. The dual carbon-skeleton entry strategy (acetaldehyde-based Strecker and pyruvate-based reductive amination) directly mirrors the two major axes identified in the research. The network's 5 hub molecules (pyruvate, acetaldehyde, HCN, aminonitrile, DL-alanine) create excellent convergence with 8 independent routes to DL-alanine. Literature alignment is outstanding\u2014nearly every major experimental study cited in the deep research (Miller 1953, Barge et al. 2019, Kaur et al. 2024, Schlikker et al. 2024, Green et al. 2023, Diederich et al. 2023, Novikov & Copley 2013, Dherbassy et al. 2023, Parker et al. 2011, Hazen et al. 2001) finds a corresponding reaction node. Key weaknesses: (1) CO\u2082\u2192pyruvate (rxn_001) is oversimplified\u2014this is typically multi-step even in the most favorable systems; (2) pyridoxal (mol_016) appears without a synthesis route, undermining P3 and P5 self-sufficiency; (3) the final L-alanine enrichment step via calcite adsorption is the acknowledged weakest link\u2014DFT calculations show <1 kcal/mol selectivity, and the literature is explicit that strong ee requires amplification mechanisms not modeled here. The network honestly addresses this as the central bottleneck. The environmental flow from Hydrothermal (CO\u2082 fixation) \u2192 Surface (Strecker, discharge) \u2192 Biochemical (transamination, chiral selection) is well-structured. Cross-environment pathways (P7, P9) are particularly strong design elements.\",\n  \"approved\": true,\n  \"hub_quality\": 0.93,\n  \"convergence_quality\": 0.